SIMPLE: miliary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miliary
<hw>Mil"ia*ry</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>miliarius</ets>, fr. <ets>milium</ets> millet: cf. F.
<ets>miliaire</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Like millet seeds; <as>as, a <ex>miliary</ex>
eruption</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Accompanied with an eruption like
millet seeds; <as>as, a <ex>miliary</ex> fever</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Small and numerous; <as>as, the
<ex>miliary</ex> tubercles of Echini</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miliary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Miliary
<hw>Mil"ia*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the
small tubercles of Echini.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milice</ent>⟦br⟧
